pull_request.title: Enable proxy tunneling
pull_request.body:
By simply using 'caw' module to create the HTTP agent with proxy settings
we are able to use 'pnpm' behind a basic corporate proxy (I could not test
it extensively on any kind of proxy).

I had to disable 'sepia' caching in case a proxy configuration is found
because it was not behaving fine with the new HTTP agent setup.

issue.title: Default listing template shows wrong url
issue.body:
I use the default listing template to output the headings of a specific category. The main title is the name of the category. But the url's of the entries are something else than supposed. For example:

- I have an entry with the url /poem/poem1
- Instead of that, Bolt puts out /blog/poem1

When creating the content, I only selected 'poem' as the category to save in. I do have a category 'blog' (but didn't select that when saving the entry). Bolt puts out the wrong url on the listing page. When I click on a title, Bolt redirects me to the content, but the url is wrong and I don't want that. What am I doing wrong?

issue.title: NetBeans 8.1, no Use Custom Test Suite checkbox
issue.body:
I can run phpunit fine from the command line but would like to run it from NetBeans.

In NetBeans, I go to Project Properties > Testing, but there is no Use Custom Test Suite checkbox. I see an Add Folder button, which can add a folder to Test Directories, and under Testing Providers there is a checkbox for PHPUnit.

I also have installed NetBeans 8.1, PHP 5.6,  PHPUnit  5.2.9, and ci-phpunit-test 11.0 on the Linux client Ubuntu 14.04 LTS.

comment.body:
I fixed the instruction: https://github.com/kenjis/ci-phpunit-test/commit/5c09ce3b3da32a7780e141595bde9fb9294391f5
Thank you for your reporting.
